7	
8	// The vendor WRITER (mount/DESIGN.md): converge a consumer's .claudinite/shared/
9	// to this canon tree's vendor set and advance the stamp — the local half of the
10	// transactional update. Callers: the adoption flow and an on-demand refresh run
11	// it from a freshly fetched canon tree against the consumer checkout; the
12	// nightly's fleet integration performs the equivalent writes over the API.
13	// Convergence is unconditional and whole-set: shared/ is rebuilt from the set
14	// (stale files vanish, local edits revert), .claudinite/local_packs/ and
15	// everything else in the consumer is untouched. Errors abort BEFORE any write —
16	// the repo keeps running its old snapshot (the transactional contract).
17	//
18	// Convergence is direction-blind (copy-if-different), so a canon checkout behind
19	// main would silently REWIND the member's whole corpus and stamp it newer (#328).
20	// Two guards refuse that before any write, when the canon root carries git
