1	#!/usr/bin/env node
2	// Adoption interviews — the mandatory questions a pack asks when a project
3	// adopts it. A pack that needs the project's INTENT before it can provide value
4	// (barriers with no graph is a silent no-op) declares its questions in an
5	// optional `questions` field on its pack.mjs:
6	//
7	//   questions: [{ id: 'goals', prompt: '…', distill: '…' }]
8	//
9	// Stable-id'd, because the answers live VERBATIM on the pack's entry in
10	// .claudinite-checks.json (`answers: { "<question-id>": "<answer>" }` — see
11	// checks/README.md): the settings file records the project's intent beside the
12	// `config` distilled from it. The GAP — declared question ids minus answered
13	// ids — drives the asking: at adoption every question is pending; when the
14	// canon later adds a question to a pack, just that one surfaces in every
15	// consumer; a pack with no questions adds nothing. An answered question stays
16	// answered — "n/a, none wanted" is an answer, distinct from never-asked.
17	//
18	//   node interview.mjs check   SessionStart step: when active packs have
19	//                              unanswered questions, emit a MILD context note
20	//                              asking the assistant to interview the owner at a
21	//                              natural moment — and telling an unattended
22	//                              session to ignore it entirely. Deliberately
23	//                              never a conformance finding: a nightly run must
24	//                              not be blocked on a question nobody is present
25	//                              to answer. Strictness lives only in the
26	//                              bootstrap adoption flow (bootstrap.md Part 6),
27	//                              where the owner is present by construction.
28	import { pathToFileURL } from 'node:url';
29	import { loadPacks, isActive } from './registry.mjs';
30	import { loadConfig } from '../checks/lib/context.mjs';
31	
32	// A pack's declared questions, validated: `questions` must be an array of
33	// { id, prompt, distill? } with non-empty string ids and prompts, ids unique
34	// within the pack. A malformed entry is reported and skipped — one bad question
